'''Euro key''' (German: Euroschlüssel) is a locking system, which has been introduced in 1986 by the [[CBF Darmstadt]] - Club Behinderter und Freunde in Darmstadt and environs, and is now uniform throughout Germany, Austria and Switzerland. It enables people with physical [[disability|disabilities]] to access their handicapped facilities and facilities free of charge For example public toilets at motorways and train stations, but also for public toilets in pedestrian zones, museums or public authorities (partly also in special elevators to ensure accessibility). A total of 12,000 locks has been fitted throughout Europe<ref>[http://verwaltung.uni-koeln.de/abteilung23/content/behinderung_und_studium/glossar___behinderung_und_studium/]</ref>
[[File:Eurokey sign, Palace of Schönbrunn (cropped).svg|border|right|200px|at [[Schönbrunn Palace]]]]

