Ethnic '''[[Georgians]] in [[Belarus]]''' number exactly 2,400 as of the country's 2009 census, and live mainly in the capital [[Minsk]]. They mainly came during the [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] era as labor migrants, or were displaced during Soviet relocation.<ref>[http://diaspora.gov.ge/?p=7820 Georgians in Belarus]</ref>

They are keeping their cultural heritage, speak [[Georgian language]] and belong to [[Georgian Orthodox Church]].

